sql:
SELECT SUM(amount) AS total_allocated_amount
FROM funding_allocations
WHERE department_id = 0;

SELECT source_name, description
FROM funding_sources
WHERE active_status = 1;

SELECT status, update_date, updated_by, notes
FROM request_statuses
WHERE request_id = 1;

SELECT source_id, SUM(total_amount) AS total_funding
FROM total_funding
GROUP BY source_id;

SELECT source_id, SUM(amount) AS total_amount
FROM funding_allocations
GROUP BY source_id;

external_knowledge:
Largest chunk of funding refers to the highest amount allocated to a department within a fiscal year; Fiscal year refers to the operational period used by the organization for accounting purposes, often denoted as FY followed by the year (e.g., FY 2020).;
Departments are organizational units within the entity managing different aspects of its operations. Each department has a unique ID and a name.；
The total amount allocated refers to the sum of all funding allocations to a department in a fiscal year.；

sql:
SELECT funding_requests.department_id, funding_requests.request_id, request_statuses.status
FROM funding_requests
JOIN request_statuses ON funding_requests.request_id = request_statuses.request_id;

SELECT DISTINCT d.department_name, d.contact_email
FROM departments d
JOIN funding_requests fr ON d.department_id = fr.department_id;
